5000|$|A crew {{dispatcher}} is also {{employed by}} the railroad to keep track <b>of</b> <b>train</b> <b>crews</b> and their assignments. The crew dispatcher is responsible for assigning <b>train</b> <b>crew</b> to <b>trains,</b> based on a crew book that shows scheduled rosters but also making real-time adjustments as necessary based on rail traffic conditions and delays. The crew dispatcher is normally assisted by a crew caller whose responsibility is to telephone the <b>train</b> and engine <b>crews</b> to advise them of time to report for duty. The crew dispatcher is also responsible for checking that each <b>train</b> and engine <b>crew</b> are properly qualified for their assignments and have had proper rest pursuant to relevant hours-of-service regulations. :3 ...|$|R
